### PolyCheck – Tests de fumée (VS Code REST Client)
### Extension requise : humao.rest-client
### Usage : cliquez sur "Send Request" au-dessus de chaque requête

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3001
@pythonUrl = http://localhost:8000

# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# HEALTH CHECKS
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 1. Health Backend
GET {{baseUrl}}/health
Accept: application/json

###

### 2. Health Service Python AST
GET {{pythonUrl}}/health
Accept: application/json

###

# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# ANALYSE – CAS NOMINAUX
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 3. Analyser du code Python avec bugs + sécurité
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/analyze
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "code": "import os\n\npassword = \"admin123\"\napi_key = \"sk-live-abcdef123456\"\n\ndef divide(a, b):\n    return a / b\n\ndef process_data(data):\n    try:\n        result = eval(data)\n        return result\n    except:\n        pass\n\ndef very_long_function(a, b, c, d, e, f, g, h):\n    x = a + b\n    y = c + d\n    z = e + f\n    w = g + h\n    if x == True:\n        return x == None\n    return x + y + z + w\n",
  "language": "python",
  "filename": "security_test.py"
}

###

### 4. Analyser du code JavaScript
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/analyze
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "code": "const password = 'secret123';\n\nfunction fetchUser(id) {\n  const query = 'SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = ' + id;\n  return db.execute(query);\n}\n\nconst apiKey = 'sk-live-abcdef1234567890';\nconsole.log('API Key:', apiKey);\n",
  "language": "javascript",
  "filename": "app.js"
}

###

### 5. Analyser du code TypeScript
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/analyze
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "code": "// TODO: fix this later\nfunction calculateTotal(items: any[]): number {\n  let total = 0;\n  for (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {\n    total = total + items[i].price;\n  }\n  return total;\n}\n\nexport default calculateTotal;\n",
  "language": "typescript",
  "filename": "utils.ts"
}

###

### 6. Analyser du code Go
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/analyze
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "code": "package main\n\nimport (\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"os/exec\"\n)\n\nfunc runCommand(input string) {\n\tcmd := exec.Command(\"sh\", \"-c\", input)\n\tout, _ := cmd.Output()\n\tfmt.Println(string(out))\n}\n\nfunc main() {\n\tpassword := \"admin\"\n\tfmt.Println(password)\n\trunCommand(\"ls -la\")\n}\n",
  "language": "go",
  "filename": "main.go"
}

###

# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# ANALYSE – CAS LIMITES (doivent retourner des erreurs propres)
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 7. Fichier vide → doit retourner HTTP 400
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/analyze
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "code": "",
  "language": "python"
}

###

### 8. Code uniquement espaces → doit retourner HTTP 400
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/analyze
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "code": "   \n\t\n   ",
  "language": "python"
}

###

### 9. Langage non supporté → doit retourner HTTP 422
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/analyze
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "code": "IDENTIFICATION DIVISION.\nPROGRAM-ID. HelloWorld.",
  "language": "cobol"
}

###

### 10. Champ code manquant → doit retourner HTTP 400
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/analyze
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "language": "python"
}

###

### 11. Champ language manquant → doit retourner HTTP 400
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/analyze
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "code": "print('hello')"
}

###

